The [[Seattle Mariners]] took part in both the [[Major League Baseball]] [[Rule 4 draft]] and the [[Rule 5 draft]] in {{mlby|2009}}.<ref name="mlb"/><ref name="rule 5"/>
The [[2009 Major League Baseball Draft]] was held June 9 to June 11 at the [[MLB Network]] Studios in [[New York City]].<ref>{{cite web|title= Draft Date and Location|url=http://www.mymlbdraft.com/2009-mlb-draft-date/|work=|archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/5iejgFXgc|archivedate=2009-07-30|deadurl=no|accessdate=2009-04-26}}</ref> The Seattle Mariners went second in the draft order and had two supplemental first-round draft picks for the loss of [[free agent]] [[RaÃºl IbÃ¡Ã±ez]] after the {{mlby|2008}} season.<ref name="2009 draft">{{cite web|url=http://www.baseball-reference.com/draft/index.cgi?draft_round=1&year_ID=2009&draft_type=junreg&query_type=year_round|title=1st Round of the 2009 June Draft|work=Baseball-Reference.com|publisher=Sports Reference LLC|accessdate=2009-11-18}}</ref> The Mariners selected a total of 52 players and signed 35 of those selected players.<ref name="mlb"/>
The Mariners selected one player in the [[Rule_5_draft_results#Major_League_Phase|Major League Baseball phase]] of the 2009 Rule 5 draft.<ref name="rule 5"/> They also had one player selected ([[Marshall Hubbard]]) in the 2009 Triple-A phase of the Rule 5 draft.<ref name="rule 5"/> The Mariners also selected one player in the Triple-A phase of the draft as well.<ref name="rule 5"/>
